    • Method Detail

      • authorize

        public OAuth2AuthorizeRespDTO authorize(OAuth2AuthorizeReqDTO oAuth2AuthorizeReqDTO)
        Process the authorization request and issue an authorization code or access token depending on the Response Type available in the request.
        Parameters:
        oAuth2AuthorizeReqDTO - OAuth2AuthorizeReqDTO containing information about the authorization request.
        Returns:
        OAuth2AuthorizeRespDTO instance containing the access token/authorization code or an error code.

      • validateClientInfo

        public OAuth2ClientValidationResponseDTO validateClientInfo(String clientId,
                                                            String callbackURI)
        Check Whether the provided client_id and the callback URL are valid.
        Parameters:
        clientId - client_id available in the request, Not null parameter.
        callbackURI - callback_uri available in the request, can be null.
        Returns:
        OAuth2ClientValidationResponseDTO bean with validity information, callback, App Name, Error Code and Error Message when appropriate.

      • issueAccessToken

        public OAuth2AccessTokenRespDTO issueAccessToken(OAuth2AccessTokenReqDTO tokenReqDTO)
        Issue access token in exchange to an Authorization Grant.
        Parameters:
        tokenReqDTO - OAuth2AccessTokenReqDTO representing the Access Token request
        Returns:
        OAuth2AccessTokenRespDTO representing the Access Token response
